<paragraph id="45DDC0F154116B498EE78DCDAC92E6D2" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">
<taxonomicName id="F27CCC6329198114EB795D215BDA4032" authority="Hudson" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="477" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="strigosa">
Carex 
<normalizedToken id="BB2A4B051A46EEE8FBE317218415F188" originalValue="strigósa" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">strigosa</normalizedToken>
Hudson
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4168DE9CB87A59F002E58B043286CE1B" pageId="null" pageNumber="477" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="3702B771C245780A786A4F7340CB9547" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">Magere Segge</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="D2E4C1789F701C9A8E97EB6E8EF919E4" pageId="null" pageNumber="477" type="description">
<paragraph id="331B4FFB47E3DEB046072B58A26D8A27" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">
20-70 cm hoch; horstbildend. Habitus wie bei 
<taxonomicName id="E3D5528BA8E008F59DC174D5B1DCDDA5" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="477" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="silvatica">
<emphasis id="16930FF840C5600FB2A3C28DE08DCF38" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">C. silvatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 80), die 
<normalizedToken id="8FFB5E87B6E1706E91614F0B0BCDF0E2" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
jedoch meist breiter (bis 10 mm breit). 
<normalizedToken id="F5EC52C0AA0380BC154BDC44170157FB" originalValue="Blütenstand" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">Bluetenstand</normalizedToken>
, Hoch- und 
<normalizedToken id="F2C8687ACDCAFA4D6D7DF37C13DE1842" originalValue="Tragblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">Tragblaetter</normalizedToken>
wie bei 
<emphasis id="960A3BFFB3EB1561C92A6F9AFDB8449A" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">
<taxonomicName id="75B303774BE1DB073B1E2219FFEC748F" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="477" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="silvatica">C. silvatica</taxonomicName>
. 
<normalizedToken id="57141AED38D21AF01BBA693068D3DDEA" originalValue="Fruchtschläuche" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">Fruchtschlaeuche</normalizedToken>
3-4 mm lang
</emphasis>
, in der Mitte am breitesten (1-1,2 mm), 3kantig, mit 
<emphasis id="90FA1F9E9A8EC7950FF31BDD7BC7E9F4" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">zahlreichen, vortretenden Nerven</emphasis>
, gelbbraun, matt, 
<emphasis id="EC574969CBF6475E632346E54E1CCE2A" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">
<normalizedToken id="83D9EB89E632ADD290AFD3FFBC2C1881" originalValue="allmählich" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">allmaehlich</normalizedToken>
in den undeutlichen Schnabel
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="061547F78D7F7BE0B1D35AB84CC64F89" originalValue="verschmälert" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">verschmaelert</normalizedToken>
. Narben 3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C9342B1AA9887AD8031908C38A9BBEF6" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">
<emphasis id="524817A4308681AADC48C5CBF4904976" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">Zytologische Angaben. 2n = 66:</emphasis>
Material aus botanischen 
<normalizedToken id="4DB824B7199D786744D274EF26F9A0CE" originalValue="Gärten" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">Gaerten</normalizedToken>
(Heilborn 1939), aus England (Davies 1956a).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="796212CCE039BA3AC60E7C8A492F95A8" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">
<emphasis id="AC7085DCBF5A0A473BCA8AE61C06488F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">Standort.</emphasis>
Kollin und montan. Nasse, 
<normalizedToken id="FBF4C5C8F112AC1E2AF3E4FB3F10E5F7" originalValue="wasserzügige" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">wasserzuegige</normalizedToken>
(quellige) kalkarme, humose Ton- und 
<normalizedToken id="F6C8E01BCBA8D4BA95706A6663B13F61" originalValue="Lehmböden" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">Lehmboeden</normalizedToken>
. 
<normalizedToken id="1650887A8B219541596AE0292E7403EB" originalValue="Bacheschenwälder" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">Bacheschenwaelder</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="CD0C9F7EF32194E7E99001E9783092E2" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">Carici remotae-Fraxinetum</emphasis>
W. Koch 1926). In Norddeutschland auch auf kalkreichen 
<normalizedToken id="0F23D9C0BA676BBE93284FBA79D4631E" originalValue="Böden" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">Boeden</normalizedToken>
und auch 
<normalizedToken id="CC569B4BDE57344E95E88CAD2EFDC249" originalValue="außerhalb" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">ausserhalb</normalizedToken>
des Bacheschenwaldes an Waldwegen (
<normalizedToken id="95F9BDCD924CF63608F268ABE4A73F56" originalValue="Rühl" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">Ruehl</normalizedToken>
1958).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="96EFA22D7BB2E041E770DE5D7A9A6BC1" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">
<emphasis id="16BDA0645120E4A8A69F6424576CBF68" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">
Verbreitung. 
<normalizedToken id="FC2CA2C1BFE02E6266562D5E702E5310" originalValue="Europäische" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">Europaeische</normalizedToken>
Pflanze:
</emphasis>
Nordwest- und Mitteleuropa (
<normalizedToken id="27297BF4B0B912D0244C5F800E1BD5E2" originalValue="Südgrenze" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">Suedgrenze</normalizedToken>
durch 
<normalizedToken id="04B45187A1D6971B59B04CC42DF79A7F" originalValue="Pyrenäen" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">Pyrenaeen</normalizedToken>
, Mittelitalien, Balkanhalbinsel); Kaukasus, 
<normalizedToken id="732D46A0D11E5D0811CD7C6D6DD8D870" originalValue="Südwestasien" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">Suedwestasien</normalizedToken>
(Persien). - Im Gebiet: Alpenvorland (Molasseberge), Mittelland, Jura (
<normalizedToken id="E8426D385F69CF2AD7DE86E57F914708" originalValue="Dép" pageId="null" pageNumber="477">Dep</normalizedToken>
. Doubs, Berner Jura, Solothurner und Aargauer Jura), Gebiet von Belfort, Sundgau, Vogesen, Oberrheinische Tiefebene, Basel (Bruderholz), Schwarzwald.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
